sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091146
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The LuxR binding site is from BBa_R0062 and the pLas' promoter is from the region upstream of the LasI gene in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: K091146 is a modified version of the pLas' promoter (BBa_K091117) containing the addition of a luxR binding site between the -35 and -10 regions. This promoter is expected to be activated in the presence of PAI-1 and LasR and repressed in the presence of AI-1 and LuxR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The Lux box was placed adjacent to the LasR binding site with the aim of minimizing cross-talk in the presence of both PAI-1 and AI-1; since the LasR site should have a higher affinity, we hope that the binding of PAI-1 will competitively exclude the binding of AI-1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Feeney

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K376010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source for luxR was the registry
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a translational unit comprised of the Lux regulatory protein with a strong RBS (B0034) ahead of it.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The RBS was added using PCR primer extension.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Anisha Katyal, Andrew Kirk, Erik McCann, Lauren Rossi, Becky Hennessey

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
